headline: 3 Reasons MAR is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, Marriott’s shares (currently trading at $265.40) have posted a disappointing 8% loss, well below the S&P 500’s 5.2% gain. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
